name: Steven Greenberg
text: Great company. Shane, the owner gives it a personal touch. All of the guys are awesome. I have three planes, of course my favorite is my fighter and I trust these guys to the moon and back, literally.  Honest  and knowledgeable, they stand behind their work.  Highly recommended!

name: Maggie Hardin
text: Amazing and knowledgeable aircraft mechanics. Super clean and efficient.

name: Jonathan McCormick
text: Fighter Maintenance Contracting is always a pleasure to work with. The crew is full of knowledgeable and experienced craftsman that I have worked with for years. They are truly an amazing group of guys with a great reputation. I give them my highest recommendation for all of your aircraft maintenance and avionics needs.

name: Adam Horn
text:
I have been flying 4 L-39s for over a year that are all maintained by Shane and his team at Fighter Maintenance Contracting. Due to their expertise, professionalism, and uncompromising safety standards, I never had to cancel a single flight for maintenance, and the jets were always 100% safe for flight.

If you are looking for someone who is honest and trustworthy to maintain your aircraft, look no further than Shane Phillips and his team at FMC!

name: Noel Y.
text: By far the best and most inclusive support I have ever had the pleasure of. Piece of mind every time I hit the start Button.  Thank you FMC.

name: David Kraft
text: Spectacular Results Oriented team. Flexible solutions and fun to work with.

name: Ron Staley
text: I have worked with Shane and his team for over 6 years on my L39.   Professional, honest, VERY and ALWAYS helpful are only a few of the words I can offer.    His access to resources have always made resolution of problems a minor issue.   All businesses should be run this way.

name: M P
text: Top notch group of patriotic maintenance professionals. If it's a war bird era, single engine jet, then it needs to be done right the first time and that's the attitude the whole team there has.

name: Benjamin Truex
text:
Shane and I go back quite a ways in history. He was a fellow crew chief of the F-15E. I knew then that his knowledge of planes was more than what the short technical school had taught him.

Had a chance to work with Shane and 1 of his crew again in Boise, Idaho a few months back. His knowledge of the L-39 had me stunned.

The team was doing an hourly inspection and he asked me if I wanted to assist. As an Air Force F-15E with 20+ of aircraft maintenance under my belt I jumped at the offer.

The words we can't fix it or something we can't do were never used. These guys go way beyond professional.  I couldn't ask for a better experience and you can't afford not to use FMC to maintain your plane.

name: Stephen Swails
text: Shane and his crew at FMC have been supporting our L39 program since  its inception. The attitude of FMC has always been mission first and helped me produce a 98% sortie rate over the last 3 years. Absolute professionals, the best L39 shop in the country hands down.

name: Kyle Stanbro
text: We have worked with FMC for the past 3+ years and have always received the highest of quality and professional service. Their pricing is better than any other maintenance shop we have used and our pilots do not question the capability of the Jets with FMC maintaining and managing the aircraft. I if you want a highly competent and respected company to maintain and manage your aircraft, FMC is 5-STAR. THANKS FOR ALL YOU DO.

name: Zachary Hassan
text: The motto has always been extremely simple: "There not ready for me" which embodies the whole mission mentality behind FMC. Every Airplane is as important as thier Friends who drive them "It's kind of a big deal every time a jet breaks ground it better be right because you only get one chance". Simply put can you trust your life and your families future to your jet mechanic? You can if when its the FMC crew! A&P certified with over 14 years Aircraft maintenance experience.

name: Jay Charlebois
text: I have been flying professionally maintained L39's from FMC since early 2014. I have definitely received the most outstanding service, militarily or civilian, from Shane Phillips and his amazing crew. FMC brings decades of vast knowledge and experience to the aviation plate. I have never dealt with such a cohesive group, so mission focused yet safety oriented. I place great confidence in the FMC team and recommend them with my highest vote.  Thank you FMC for your devoted service and what you stand for in the aviation community.

name: Randall Gober
text: FMC is always spot on!!! Five Stars is not enough. As the Fbo and Airport operations,its an ease of mind to have such a first class professional group to take on whatever I ask them for. My crew is so small, I ask them for help and do some quick repairs for us , and they surprisingly do better than expected everytime.There is nothing this group want try, Never been told NO, how big or small the task is, always quick response, definetly a number on my top10 speed dial list, and very quick to respond no matter where on the planet they might be.

name: Brian Evans
text: After a career of flying F-18's in the Marine Corps, I transitioned to flying L-39's. Shane and the Fighter Maintenace Contracting team that he singlehandedly built was the highest quality of aircraft maintenance that I'd seen and FMC garnered my upmost respect and confidence.

name: Monica A.
text: This morning I took a detour onto Lockheeds county road and got stuck in a muddy area. I tried to get myself unstuck but, thay didn't work out.  A young man by the name of Mr. Orlando(Lockheeds plant manager) stopped to help me. He found a solution to my problem. Another young man by the name of Mr. Mike stopped to help. With the help of Mr. Mikes chain and truck both men worked together to pull my car out of the muddy area. What seemed to be a horrible morning for me actually turned out to be a display of heroic kindness for a damsel in distress. To you both, thank you for doing something I've seen my father do for years; lend a helping hand to someone in need. You guys didn't have to stop but you did. Not one time did you guys hesitate to help me. I really appreciate you both.
